<p>I have to delete all the pdf files which are more than 30 days old at 11:30 PM</p>  <p>The below given are the two working cronjobs in <code>/etc/crontab</code></p>  <pre><code>30 23 * * * root find /var/www/html/site/reports/ -name ".pdf" -type f -mtime +30 | xargs -I {} rm -f {} \;  30 23 * * * root find /var/www/html/site/reports/ ( -name ".pdf" ) -type f -mtime +30 -exec rm {} \; </code></pre>  <p>I would like to know which one is better among the two and the reason.</p>  <p>Please help.</p>